2. cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) - The paper discusses the impact of rate-splitting and channel knowledge at the transmitters, which are important topics in networking and internet architecture. 
3. cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) - The paper analyzes interference networks, which can be modeled as social and information networks. 
4. cs.MM (Multimedia) - The paper may discuss the impact of interference on multimedia applications in interference networks. 
5. cs.CE (Computational Engineering, Finance, and Science) - The paper may use computational methods to analyze the DMT for interference networks.
